snippet.textDisplay: Ipad pro is an incredible device. Do you need one ? It is really a question of way of life. During last 5 years for professional reasons my life has been ultra mobile. Meaning spending most of it in hotels, planes, far from home, I've tried plenty of solutions and at the end I always go back to an Ipad pro.Why ? Ratio between form factor/ power and versatility. I am not a professional video editor (but I can use Lumafusion if needed) and for the rest I've found a solution to all my needs in a device that can be always in my backpack. After If you work at a desk, go home every evening, forget it, a mac book air will do the job, will be cheaper and more confortable in this context. For sure, I will purchase the new keyboard, because I hate my always dirty Ipad screen.

I have a 1st gen IPad Pro 11.7” new in 2016. So whatever model that is....*lol* while I enjoy my IPad and 2015 MacBook Pro for certain tasks, I use windows everyday too.
The IPad has cellular service at much lower cost than any laptop and windows still doesn’t offer a decent price on cellular service...so behind the curve.
My IPad is for consumption and some productivity but since getting files off is difficult (I depend on Dropbox) I don’t really use it for productivity...Biggest reason I use the Apple ecosystem is the fact that phone, pad, macbook is seamless and it works...(99 percent of the time). I would like the 2020 IPad Pro but I’ll wait a few more years and see how the software evolves. Apple has been wrecking the user interface and making major errors that are turning cold to continue counting on them for long term. However MSFT is much worse so they really are the only seamless game that is decent.

snippet.textDisplay: I had a MS Surface tablet/laptop at work for about a year. The one that has the folio keyboard and disconnects to be a tablet.  It was a terrible product and my work finally got me a standard HP laptop now since I had so many issues and complaints.
